<TEXTAREA NAME="ReplyMessage" ROWS=20 COLS=75 WRAP="VIRTUAL">[QUOTE]Originally posted by DevanRobS:
[I]don't get me wrong this is a very fun and in some ways deep game. I just finished the game and i was a little disappointed. The whole thing was incredible until after you become the divine one. At that point it is just kill kill kill, not that theres anything wrong with that but larian put way to much in at the ending to a point where it became repetitive and boring. Before your the divine one you can take you time and explore and do side quests in rivertown, if you haven't beaten the game i suggest you do all the fun stuff you want before you become the divine one because you will be in for a crap load of fighting. Overall though the game was excellent and i would give it a perfect score if it wasn't for the out of place ending.[/I][/QUOTE]

